article.headline: Cleveland St. 63, Youngstown State 50
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Patrick Tatham scored 16 points and had the first basket in a 16-2 second-half spurt to lead Cleveland State to a 63-50 victory over Youngstown State on Saturday night. J'Nathan Bullock added 14 points for the Vikings (6-8, 2-3 Horizon League). Keston Roberts, coming off a 28-point effort in a loss to Wright State on Thursday night, led the Penguins (5-11, 2-4) with 13 points. Quin Humphrey had 9 points and 11 rebounds. Youngstown State's only lead was at 32-31 at the 16:22 mark of the second half after Dwight Holmes hit a jumper. Tatham followed with a basket that put the Vikings ahead to stay. While the Penguins failed to score, Justin Henderson had a basket, Raheem Moss and Carlos English each hit a 3-pointer, Bullock had a three-point play and Frashon McGee hit another 3 to close the surge. The Vikings led by as many as 16 points in the final minutes.
